Cherry Brown Betty
  --@wickdconfections

Filling:
6 c fresh or frozen cherries, pitted (900 g)
3/4 c  sugar (150 g)
1/4 c brown sugar (50 g)
1 tbsp lemon juice (15 ml)
1 tsp vanilla extract (5 ml)
1 tsp cinnamon (2–3 g)
1/4 tsp nutmeg (optional)
1/4 tsp salt
1–1 1/2 tbsp cornstarch (8–12 g)
2 tbsp cold water (30 ml)
6 c challah bread, cut into 3/4" cubes (~300 g)
3/4 c unsalted butter, melted (170 g)
1/2 c brown sugar (100 g)
1 tsp cinnamon
Pinch of salt

Preheat oven to 350F / 175C and butter a 9×13" in (23×33 cm) dish. Mix cherries, sugars, lemon juice, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt. Stir in a slurry made from cornstarch + cold water. Toss challah cubes with melted butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, and salt. Spread half in dish, add cherry filling, top with remaining cubes. 

Topping:
1  1/2c fresh breadcrumbs (75 g)
1/4 c brown sugar (50 g)
1/4 c unsalted butter, melted (57 g)
1/4 tsp cinnamon
Pinch salt

Mix and sprinkle over the top. Bake 45–55 min until golden and bubbling. Rest 15–20 min before serving.

